@endnode

@node "History" "History"
 History:

And now the history, which have to be now at version v1.3 of BootMon.

The idea for the program came from the BootExecutor, which @{"I" link "Adresse" 0} wrote, too. This
program has start the actual bootblock and returns after that. But one day I
want to make more than only start bootblocks. I want to edit bootblocks
easily. Now comes birthday of BootMonitor.

Here are the versions of BootMonitor:

V1.0 is described above.

V1.1 no publication, Beta-Version. I fixed only a little bug.

V1.2 no publication, Beta-Version. I include a little safe against viruses.

@{"V1.3" link "Version13" 0} I can offer.

@{"V1.4" link "Version14" 0} is available since 26.04.1996.

@{"V1.5" link "Version15" 0} is available since 19.05.1996.

@{"V1.6" link "Version16" 0} is available since 28.05.1996.

@{"V1.7" link "Version17" 0} is available since 02.06.1996.

@{"ForĀtheĀfutureĀofĀBootMonitor" link "Future" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Version13" "Version13"
 To version 1.3:

Fixed a bug, which has had disastrous effects on pressing strange hotkeys. The
bootmon traveled to guruland then. The reason was only a bug in the sequence
of requests for hotkeys. This bug was fixed in v1.1 already. In v1.2 I have
included some changes and safety request, how I described above. At v1.3
BootMon has a menu. The little problems with fonts in previous versions are
fixed. The hotkeys are the same, but you have to be pressed the right Amiga
key, too, because the hotkeys included to the menu. Furthermore the editor was
changed. A new menu named "CURSOR" are appearing, which can control only the
editor. Now the hotkeys

             CTRL-W
      CTRL-A        CTRL-S
             CTRL-Y
             CTRL-Z

have no function. Thats the new keys:

           RAMIGA-8
   RAMIGA-4        RAMIGA-6
           RAMIGA-2

The control is now more comfortable. Owner of an A600 can use the normal
numbers on the keyboard or the menu. Owner of Kickstart 1.3 has only limited
control on the programm, or they have an ASL.library. The asl.library will be
used for filerequesters. If you have no such library, you can`t use the:

        Gadgets: Archive BB
                 UnArchive BB

and the
          Menus: Load BB
                 Write BB

otherwise you can use the program usually. Furthermore BootMon has small
function for safety:

1. BootMonitor checks before the start the vectors of CoolCapture, ColdCapture
etc. and a message appears, if anything is wrong. Then you will be request for
reset these vectors.

2. After the start of a bootblock the vectors will be checked, too.

3. The request will be appear, too, if anything is wrong.

4. On quitting the BootMon will check the vectors again and request a message,
if anything is wrong. Furthermore the programm requests for really quitting.

5. If the systemvectors are changed hardly, a beep sounds.

6. The Images are situated in a drawer named "BImages/".

7. Now the packet contains these files:

        BootMon                  : The BootMonitor itself
        BootMon.info             : The icon for BootMonitor
        BootMon.dok              : The documentation of BootMon
        BootMon.dok.info         : The icon for the documentation
        @{fg highlight}BImages@{fg text}                  : The drawer for the images
         BImages/Archive.image   : intern icon
         BImages/Clear.image     : intern icon
         BImages/Device.image    : intern icon
         BImages/Edit.image      : intern icon
         BImages/Execute.image   : intern icon
         BImages/Exit.image      : intern icon
         BImages/Info.image      : intern icon
         BImages/Read.image      : intern icon
         BImages/Reset.image     : intern icon
         BImages/Show.image      : intern icon
         BImages/UnArchive.image : intern icon
         BImages/Undo.image      : intern icon
         BImages/Vektor.image    : intern icon
         BImages/Write.image     : intern icon

Now viruses have no chance on your system, but you can let changed vectors,
because BootMon requests you for that.

BootMonitor V1.3 is no more FREEWARE, but GIFTWARE, that means the author
looks forward to little attentions, letters, responses or even financial
gifts. You should copy free BootMon v1.3. Should this program places on
PD-Series, so you must not ask for more than costs for discs and copy (ca. 35
ųS,5 DM or 3 dollars). You must not distribute the BootMon in commercial ways.
You can send a stamped envelope and a 3,5" disc tp the author, and you receive
a little programm from @{"A.C.M.ĀtheĀAssembler-Magician" link "Adresse" 0}. Please wrote your
entirely address onto this envelope. Incomplete addresses or any postboxes I
see like contribution for beneficence. My  @{"Adress" link "Adresse" 0} is described above. If you
will send me Mail from Countries, who have another Language as German, you can
also write in ENGLISH (because it will possible, that i have my difficultes to
understand you :-), thank you.
@endnode

@node "Version14" "Version14"
