@node "Version15" "Version15"
 To version 1.5 of BootMonitor:

Now BootMonitor can read bootblocks from other than the `trackdisk.device`.
You can define that in the item @{"Device" link "Device" 0}. Warning, BootMonitor can`t read from
higher devicenumbers, like p.e.: 4.

The Copyright is the same like in @{"VersionĀ1.4" link "Version14" 0}, but registered users can update
the program. The price of an update from version 1.4 are only the halve,
therefore 50,-- ųS or 7,50 DM or 5 U$. Unregistered users have to pay for the
full-version the same price like in version 1.4 100,-- ųS or 10,-- DM or 10
U$.

The shareware version may/should/must be free copieable like version 1.4 for
PD-Series, mailboxes, CD`s etc. You must not distribute the BootMon in
commercial kind or at discs, without knowing of the @{"Author" link "Adresse" 0}. You must not
change the BootMon, because that`s a criminal act. But it`s allowed to
translate the guides and docs and include thenm to the packet. If you send me
a translated doc, you can get a full-version of BootMon v1.5. The intern icons
of BootMon are subject to the copyright, too.
@endnode

@node "Version16" "Version16"
 To version 1.6 of BootMon:

Now the BootMon can save bootblocks in memory as executable files.

Warning, the bootblock can also save trackloader and bootblock-viruses as
files, what can support the spreading of viruses.

Therefore the routine checks for the facility to run the files. Naturally, the
BootMon @{fg highlight}can`t@{fg text} use as Debugger or has scientific intelligence for scanning and
checking code.

Copyrights are changed:

The fullversion of BootMon version 1.6 costs now:

        200 ųs or 20 DM or 20 U$ (indepently of dollar rate).

The update from version 1.5 to version 1.6 costs for registered users:

        50 ųs or 7 DM or 5 U$.

The update from version 1.4 to version 1.6 costs for registered users:

        75 ųs or 11 DM or 7,50 U$.

Version below 1.4 of BootMon are giftware and @{fg highlight}can`t@{fg text} be updated.

The shareware versions are free copieable. It is allowed, that they consist on
CD`s, PD-series, mailboxes and so on., but not as part of commercial software.
Registrations at users of Bootmon will be handled discret.
@endnode

@node "Version17" "Version17"
 To version 1.7:

With version 1.7 you can now write executable programs into the bootblock.

See @{"Konv.ĀD." link "Konvert_File" 0}.

Therefore the output window is independent at the control window now, and I
could create a new row for gadget`s with new icons.

See @{"theĀwholeĀpacket" link "Paket" 0}.

Now on the BootMon screen are displayed more than one window, p.e. two or
three.

The first window displaying the heading of Bootmon as titel and shows
informations.

The second window names `Steuerpult` and is the really control window, with
that you can control Bootmon now. It now contains all gadget`s and menues. You
can control the editor entirely in that window, inputs from keyboard, menues,
gadget`s you can only control in that window. It`s the only window with
closegadget, with that you can leave Bootmon. Features of that windowing are
p.e. if text are displaying, then it comes automatically in the foreground and
a click with left button on controlpult or a click with right button pops the
control window to front.

If the control window bother you, so you can click it in the background, and
if it`s active yet, you can control Bootmon with the menu and editing easily.

All outputs from Bootmon will be shown in the other window. An exception is
only the calc-window, which appears only at the @{"editingĀmode" link "Edit" 0}.

The Copyrights are:

Bootmon 1.7 is shareware, and a registrations will cost a small amount, but
then you have the full version.

The full version of Bootmon version 1.7 costs:

        200 ųs or 30 DM or 20 U$ (independently of the cash rate).

An update from version1.6 to version 1.7 costs for registered users:

        50 ųs or 7 DM or 5 U$.

An update from version 1.5 to version 1.7 costs for registered users:

        75 ųs or 11 DM or 7,50 U$.

An update from version 1.4 to version 1.7 costs for registered users:

        100 ųs or 15 DM or 10 U$.

Versions below as 1.4 you can`t update, they are free copieable.
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"
 In the future I will add improvements and new features to BootMon.

At first I will allowing mor than 4 Unit`s.

Otherwise the editor will be improved.

Including a disassembler (Author searching for tips).

Including a disassemblers at copper-base to show and use copperlistings at the
bootblock.

Converting of absolute code into bootblocks to include executable programs
into bootblocks. (Is now in version 1.7 Reality.)

Converting bootblocks into executable code. (Is now in version 1.6 Reality.)

The ability for Locale-Support, that`s the Goodbye for users of Kickstart 1.3
(Sorry, but the Show must go on).

The ability to change bytes per input of scalars.

A request for passwords to put a stop to access for mediums.

All items reachable per gadgets. (Is now in version 1.7 Reality.)

The order of improvements is reserved, of course.
@endnode

